	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Excellent, thanks for your response.<br /><br />Yes, I found another source of info that stated about 1N4148...and they even mentioned 1N914.<br /><br />What about the capacitor? Is there one of that specific type? 22uF 6.3 V?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Memblers</b> [ Wed Apr 10, 2013 7:52 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: NES-SKROM Enabling battery backup feature</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The 22uF 6.3V capacitor would be an electrolytic type.  Since it's polarized just be sure to connect it the right way, the exact value isn't too important.  Using a higher voltage rated one is fine, as is a somewhat higher capacitance, 33uF 100V for example, as long as the pins fit the board.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


